text.tspan: Prevalence of tuberculosis by drug susceptibility, World, 1990 to 2017
Number of tuberculosis cases by drug susceptibility.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease Study (2017)
Note: Multidrug-resistant TB does not respond to at least the two most commonly used drugs against TB - isoniazid and rifampicin. Extensively
drug-resistant TB is resistant to isoniazid, rifampicin, any of the fluoroquinolones and any of the second-line drugs against TB.
